Link OpenFHE against the hermetic LLVM libomp instead of a system libomp.

OpenFHE enables OpenMP by default (@openfhe//:enable_openmp=True), which adds
`-fopenmp` to the compile line and `-fopenmp -lomp` to the link line, and makes
core/lib/**/*.cpp do `#include <omp.h>` (via utils/parallel.h). This assumes a
system-provided omp.h and libomp on the compiler/linker search paths.

HEIR's hermetic, bootstrapped LLVM toolchain (cerisier toolchains_llvm_bootstrapped)
ships neither: its minimal clang-22 distribution has no omp.h in the clang
resource dir and no libomp runtime anywhere, so the build fails with

  src/core/include/utils/parallel.h:40:14: fatal error: 'omp.h' file not found

and, even with the header, the link would fail on `-lomp` (no system libomp).

The same `llvm` module does expose a hermetic libomp built from the pinned LLVM
sources as @openmp//:libomp (a cc_library that also generates omp.h and exports
its include dir). The root module (HEIR) makes that repo visible to OpenFHE's
openfhe_config module extension via inject_repo() and this patch surfaces it to
OpenFHE's BUILD files as @openfhe_config//:libomp (a repo OpenFHE already sees).
A BUILD file in the openfhe module cannot name @openmp directly because that repo
is not in the openfhe module's repo mapping; routing it through the
openfhe_config repo (whose repo mapping does receive the injected @openmp) is the
visibility bridge. This patch:

  * makes the generated @openfhe_config repo export an alias `libomp` ->
    @openmp//:libomp (openfhe_config.bzl).
  * adds @openfhe_config//:libomp to the `core` cc_library deps. core is the
    transitive base of binfhe/pke, so this puts omp.h on the -I path for every
    OpenFHE compile and links the libomp archive into every OpenFHE consumer.
  * drops `-lomp`/`-fopenmp` from the clang OpenMP linkopts: the runtime now comes
    from the libomp archive dep, and there is no system libomp to name. `-fopenmp`
    is retained as a *compile* flag (it drives the #pragma omp codegen) but removed
    from the link line so the clang driver does not auto-add a search for a
    nonexistent system libomp.

Drop this patch once OpenFHE can consume a toolchain-provided OpenMP runtime
directly (e.g. an upstream @openfhe//:enable_openmp path that takes a libomp
label), or once the bootstrapped toolchain ships omp.h + libomp on its default
search paths.

diff --git a/BUILD b/BUILD
--- a/BUILD
+++ b/BUILD
@@ -59,10 +59,9 @@ config_setting(
     },
 )

-_OPENMP_CLANG_LINKOPTS = [
-    "-fopenmp",
-    "-lomp",
-]
+# libomp is provided as the @openfhe_config//:libomp archive dep (see core); the
+# hermetic toolchain has no system libomp to link via -fopenmp/-lomp.
+_OPENMP_CLANG_LINKOPTS = []

 _OPENMP_GCC_LINKOPTS = [
     "-fopenmp",
@@ -138,6 +137,7 @@ cc_library(
     deps = [
         ":generate_config_core_h",
         ":prng",
+        "@openfhe_config//:libomp",
         "@cereal",
     ],
 )
diff --git a/openfhe_config.bzl b/openfhe_config.bzl
--- a/openfhe_config.bzl
+++ b/openfhe_config.bzl
@@ -11,7 +11,12 @@ def _config_repo_impl(rctx):
     has_int128 = rctx.attr.has_int128
     mathbackend = rctx.attr.mathbackend

-    rctx.file("BUILD.bazel", 'exports_files(["config.bzl", "generate_header.sh"])')
+    # Re-export the hermetic LLVM libomp (injected into this extension as @openmp
+    # by the root module) under a name OpenFHE's own BUILD files can see. The
+    # bootstrapped clang toolchain ships no system omp.h/libomp.
+    rctx.file("BUILD.bazel", '''exports_files(["config.bzl", "generate_header.sh"])
+alias(name = "libomp", actual = "@openmp//:libomp", visibility = ["//visibility:public"])
+''')

     # Store config values in .bzl for BUILD files to use
     rctx.file("config.bzl", """
